    <summary>View All Folders Settings Of Explorer</summary>
    <description>
Each time that you open a folder in Explorer, Windows automatically save the settings of this folder into the Registry.

This utility displays the list of all folder settings saved by Windows.

For each folder, the following information is displayed: The date/time that you opened it, the entry number, 
display mode (Details, Icons, Tiles, and so on...), the last position of the window, and the last size of the window.
    </description>
